    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SRM Environment Variables</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The complete, annotated list of SRM console variables (<text styleclass="Code Example">auto_action</text>, the <text styleclass="Code Example">boot_*</text> set, <text styleclass="Code Example">com1_*</text> / <text styleclass="Code Example">com2_*</text>, the <text styleclass="Code Example">d_*</text> diagnostics group, the N1 to N16 NVRAM slots, <text styleclass="Code Example">wwid0</text> to <text styleclass="Code Example">wwid7</text>, and so on) is maintained in the appendix:</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="NotesBox">-Appendix, DS10, &quot;SRM Commands &gt;&gt;&gt; Prompt&quot;.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">These SRM variables are distinct from the emulator&apos;s own <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_*</text> launch environment variables, which are documented under the Reference section&apos;s Environment Variables page.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
